          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-537ee9a9f17c8071",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "How are GIC returns taxed?\nIf you\u2019re holding a GIC in a non-registered account, it\u2019s subject to tax each year. So, if you have a GIC with a three-year term, the interest you earn on each anniversary will be taxed \u2013 even if it hasn\u2019t been paid out to you yet. If you hold a GIC in an RRSP , you\u2019ll only pay tax when you withdraw your money.\nCan I cash in my GIC early? Yes, you can! Cashable GIC s can be redeemed before the term ends, although the window can differ according to the type of GIC . Non-cashable GIC s can\u2019t be redeemed early without paying a penalty.",
